				<td style="padding: 12px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">22%</td>
				<td style="padding: 12px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">60 mo</td>
				<td style="padding: 12px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">$275</td>
				<td style="padding: 12px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">$16,500</td>
			</tr>
		</tbody>
	</table>

	<h2>Choosing the Right Option</h2>

	<h3>Best for Small Budgets</h3>
	<p>If monthly payment is your primary concern, longer-term personal loans or HELOCs offer lowest payments (though more total interest).</p>

	<h3>Best for Minimizing Total Cost</h3>
	<p>Cash, followed by 0% promotional financing paid within the promotional period.</p>

	<h3>Best for Large Projects</h3>
	<p>HELOC typically offers best rates for projects $10,000+.</p>

	<h3>Best for Quick Approval</h3>
	<p>Contractor financing or existing credit card.</p>

	<h2>Pre-Approval Tips</h2>
	<ul>
		<li>Check your credit score before applying</li>
		<li>Compare rates from multiple lenders</li>
		<li>Get pre-approved before contractor consultations</li>
		<li>Read all terms carefully, especially promotional offer fine print</li>
		<li>Calculate total cost, not just monthly payment</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>Conclusion</h2>
	<p>The right financing option depends on your credit profile, how quickly you can pay off the balance, and your monthly budget. Don't let cost stop you from getting the fence your property needs—but do choose financing wisely to minimize long-term costs.</p>

	<p>Questions about financing your fence project? Contact us to discuss payment options available through our financing partners.</p>

